review_content:
Pros:
✅ The scent is appealing;
✅ Versatile scent profile;
✅ Inoffensive smell.

Cons:
❌ Weak Projection;
❌ Doesn't last long on my skin.

Overall Score: 6/10.
A solid fragrance but nothing groundbreaking. Can be used as an Inoffensive signature scent.

@Vanilla panda

Yes, that is exactly how I experience the fragrance, which I purchased directly from Montblanc. I love Notino, but they have ceased their US operations..
I was disappointed at first, for the same reasons that you stated, but I loved the bottle and had already sprayed it so I figured it would become part of my collection though I probably wouldn't wear it. My box/bottle happens to sit in a spot where I can easily access it so I have randomly chosen to spray a few times, for fun.. The packaging somehow stands out - even though it's just a plain pink square shaped box.. And I have to say the fragrance has started to grow on me. I still don't love it, but am staring to appreciate it - it will be a "once in a while" perfume for me, something I spray at home when I feel like I need something different. It's nice, not what I was expecting, but something I can learn to enjoy during the right moment.

@bharatbj65
What patch do you have?

It's not it's not lasting, it's that you will go nose-blind to it. Almost everyone agrees on this.
